<h1>Horses: The Majestic Runners</h1>

<p class="horse-text">
<strong>Horses</strong> are large, <em>graceful animals</em> known for their speed and strength. 
They have been <strong>companions and helpers</strong> to humans for thousands of years, used for riding, work, and sport. 
<em>They are intelligent and social creatures</em>, forming strong bonds with humans and other horses. 
This is why horses are <strong>truly magnificent</strong>!
</p>

<img src="https://cdn.kastatic.org/third_party/javascript-khansrc/live-editor/build/images/animals/horse.png" 
     alt="A brown horse running in a field" width="400" height="300">

<h1>Cats: The Curious Companions</h1>

<p class="cat-text">
<em>Cats</em> are small, agile mammals that have been human companions for thousands of years. 
They are <strong>playful, curious, and independent</strong>, yet they also enjoy cuddling with their humans. 
Cats have <strong>sharp senses</strong> and can see in low light, making them excellent hunters. 
These little creatures are <strong>both mysterious and lovable</strong>!
</p>

<img src="https://cdn.kastatic.org/third_party/javascript-khansrc/live-editor/build/images/animals/cat.png" 
     alt="A cute tabby cat sitting" width="400" height="300">


